<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 201</seg>
                                </opener>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                </head>
                                <p>British Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> and Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> traveled to Paris in
                                    mid-December for meetings with French Government officials. For
                                    a report on these meetings, see telegram 3663 from Paris,
                                    Document 457.</p>
